arXiv.abstract:
We present the first measurement of the Michel parameters $ ar{\eta}$ and $\xi\kappa$ in the radiative leptonic decay of the $	au$ lepton using 703 f$\mathrm{b}^{-1}$ of data collected with the Belle detector at the KEKB $e^+e^-$ collider. The Michel parameters are measured by an unbinned maximum likelihood fit to the kinematic information of $e^+e^-ightarrow	au^+	au^-ightarrow (\pi^+\pi^0  ar{
u})(l^-
u ar{
u}\gamma)$ $(l=e$ or $\mu)$. The preliminary values of the measured Michel parameters are $ ar{\eta} = -2.0 \pm 1.5 \pm 0.8$ and $\xi\kappa = 0.6 \pm 0.4 \pm 0.2$, where the first error is statistical and the second is systematic.

